1. How can you switch a css style when the screen size is below a certain size?
Using @media Rule
e.g
@media screen and (max-width: 479px) {
  /* Styles here will be used when the screen size is anything between 0 - 478px */
}

2. What is the benefit of using stylesheets instead of inline styles?
Easier to maintain especially for larger sites since an update reflects to all other pages. Performs well especially when the file has been cached for reusability.

3. Is there a way to manage CSS with variables and functions?
Yes, you can use parameters in the html attribute to manipulate the css of a page element with the specified custom variables and functions.

4. Review and update the following erroneous CSS:
.button, input[type="submit"], button {
position: relative
display: inline-block;
padding-front: 0;
margin: 0;
border: none;
text-decoration: none;
text-align: center;
white-space: nowrap;
overflow: visible;
bgcolor: red;
text-transform: uppercase
font-color: #fZb034;
font-size: 18px;
font-family: 'FuturaBT-Book';
line-height. 20px;
height: 20px;
-webkit-transition: color 0.2s ease-in-out;
transition: color 0.2s ease-in-out
}

/* Answer */
input[type="submit"], button {
  border: none;
  background-color: red;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  font-size: 18px;
  font-family: 'FuturaBT-Book';
  line-height: 20px;
  height: 20px;
  -webkit-transition: color 0.2s, ease-in-out 0.2s;
  transition: color 0.2s, ease-in-out 0.2s;
}
